XV. This also is to be noted, that if any covenant is made as to the mode of executing the convention, that does not become a condi- tion of the agreement: as, if it were said that it is to be discharged in a certain place, which place afterwards changes its master.

XVI. With regard to Hostages, what we have said above is to be observed, that in general, they are accessories to the principal act: but it may be covenanted that the obligation shall be disjunctive3 that either something shall be done, or the hostages retained.
